he idealized, heroic visions of officership from the First World War. Fascinating and highly original, this book sheds new light on the challenges many junior officers faced during the Second World War – not only on the battlefield but from Canadians’ often conflicted views about social class and gender.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zCanada. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War II.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z978311127619908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311141793640uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077483485840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774834858423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774834858/original  a978-3-11-127365-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-127619-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-141793-6  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles